# Pink Tie Planner — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
A UWaterloo degree planner app. Students pick their program (major + optional double major, minor, specialization), import their transcript, and plan future courses across terms. Core features: requirement tracking, prerequisite/antireq validation, co-op sequence mapping.

---

## Tech Stack

- **Next.js 16.2.4** (App Router) — has breaking changes from older versions. Check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing any Next.js-specific code. Do not assume APIs match what you know from Next.js 13–15.
- **React 19.2.4** — use modern hooks; avoid legacy patterns
- **TypeScript 5** — strict mode enabled; no `any`, no type assertions unless unavoidable
- **Tailwind CSS 4** — used minimally; layout and component styling is done with **inline styles**, not Tailwind classes
- **fuzzysort 3.1.0** — used for course and program search; do not replace with naive string matching
- **pdf-parse** — used for transcript import in the API route
- Path alias: `@/` maps to the repo root (configured in tsconfig.json)

---

## File & Folder Structure

```
app/                        # Next.js App Router — server entry points only
  api/
    courses/route.ts        # Proxies UW Open API, 1hr in-memory cache
    parse-transcript/route.ts  # PDF transcript parser
  layout.tsx                # Root layout, DM Sans + DM Mono fonts
  page.tsx                  # Renders <App />
  globals.css               # CSS custom properties (design tokens)
src/
  components/               # All UI — all 'use client'
    App.tsx                 # Root component, wraps AppProvider
    Sidebar.tsx             # Navigation, PageId union
    Dashboard.tsx           # Program progress overview
    DegreePlan.tsx          # Requirement tree view
    CourseCatalog.tsx       # Browsable course list with search
    SemesterPlanner.tsx     # Per-term course planning
    Onboarding.tsx          # Program selection + transcript import
  context/
    AppContext.tsx           # Single global state store (React Context)
  lib/
    termUtils.ts            # Term string helpers (W25, S25, F25)
    coopSequences.ts        # Co-op stream → study label mapping
    prereqCheck.ts          # Prerequisite + antireq validation
    requirementEvaluator.ts # Recursive requirement tree evaluation
  data/
    requirements-filtered.json  # All programs with ReqNode trees
    antireqs.json               # Course antirequisite pairs
    coopSequences.ts            # Hard-coded co-op stream sequences
    invalid-combinations.json   # Program combination blockers
```

---

## Core Types

These are the canonical types. Do not redefine or shadow them.

```typescript
// AppContext.tsx
interface UserProgram {
  id: string;
  major: string;
  doubleMajor: string | null;
  doubleMajorId: string | null;
  minor: string | null;
  minorId: string | null;
  extras: ExtraCredential[];
  coopStream: '1' | '2' | '3' | '4' | 'none' | null;
  startTerm: string | null; // e.g. "F25"
}

interface ExtraCredential {
  type: 'major' | 'minor' | 'joint' | 'specialization';
  id: string;
  name: string;
}

interface CourseInfo {
  code: string;        // e.g. "CS135"
  name: string;
  description: string;
  prereqs: string;     // raw text from UW API
  antireqs: string;
  offered: string[];   // ['F', 'W', 'S']
}

// requirementEvaluator / requirements-filtered.json
interface ReqNode {
  text: string;
  type: 'AND' | 'OR' | 'N_OF' | 'COURSE' | 'ADDITIONAL';
  code?: string;    // only on COURSE nodes
  n?: number;       // only on N_OF nodes
  children?: ReqNode[];
}
```

**Term strings:** `W25`, `S25`, `F25` (Winter/Spring(co-op)/Fall, 2-digit year).
**Study labels:** `1A`, `1B`, `2A`, `2B`, `3A`, `3B`, `4A`, `4B`, `WT1`–`WT6`.

---

## State Management

Global state lives entirely in `src/context/AppContext.tsx` via React Context. There is no Redux, Zustand, or other library.

- Access state with `useApp()` — throws if called outside `<AppProvider>`
- Mutations: use provided setters (`setProgram`, `setCompletedCourses`, `setSemesterPlans`) and convenience methods (`addCourseToTerm`, `removeCourseFromTerm`, `toggleFavorite`)
- Do not reach around the context to mutate state directly
- State is persisted in **`localStorage`** under `pink-tie-planner-plan` (versioned JSON: program, completed courses, semester plans, favorites, `setupComplete`). Debounced writes + `beforeunload` flush; use `clearPersistedPlan()` from `@/src/lib/planPersistence` when adding a reset control.

---

## Component Conventions

- All components in `src/components/` are `'use client'`; add the directive at the top of every new component file
- One primary component per file; tightly related sub-components (e.g. `CheckBox`, `CourseChip`) may live in the same file
- Component names: **PascalCase**
- Utility/helper functions: **camelCase**
- Props interfaces: inline or named `Props` — keep close to the component definition
- Destructure props in the function signature: `function Foo({ bar, baz }: { bar: string; baz: number })`

---

## Styling

All layout and visual styling uses **inline styles**. Do not add Tailwind class-based styling to existing components.

**Design token palette (from globals.css):**
- Black: `#000` — text, active buttons, borders
- White: `#fff` — backgrounds, reversed text
- Gray text (inactive): `#858080`
- Gray panel/sidebar: `#ececec`
- Gray muted/disabled: `#d9d9d9`
- Pink (brand): `#c60078`
- Transparent overlays: `rgba(133,128,128,0.24)`, `rgba(255,255,255,0.45)`

**Fonts:** `DM Sans` (body), `DM Mono` (code/technical). Reference via CSS variables `--font-dm-sans` and `--font-dm-mono`.

**Hover states:** implement with `onMouseEnter`/`onMouseLeave` updating local state, then apply via inline style.

**Icons:** inline `<svg>` elements. Use Next.js `<Image>` for raster assets.

---

## Business Logic

### Term Utilities (`src/lib/termUtils.ts`)
- `getCurrentTerm()` — returns current term based on month
- `nextTerm(t: string)` — cycles W → S → F → W
- `termToNum(t: string)` — converts term to sortable number

### Co-op Sequences (`src/lib/coopSequences.ts`)
- `getStudyLabel(calTerm, startTerm, stream)` — maps a calendar term to a study label (e.g. `'2A'`, `'WT3'`)
- `computeGradTerm(startTerm, stream)` — returns the 4B graduation term
- Stream IDs: `'1'`, `'2'`, `'3'`, `'4'`, `'none'`

### Prerequisite Checking (`src/lib/prereqCheck.ts`)
- `getMissingPrereqs(prereqStr, available)` — returns unsatisfied prereqs given completed courses
- `isMathRestricted(prereqStr, userMajor?)` — detects Math-faculty-only restrictions
- `parseRequiredLevel(prereqStr)` — extracts minimum study level from prereq text
- Prereq strings come directly from the UW API (natural language); parsing is regex-based

### Requirement Evaluation (`src/lib/requirementEvaluator.ts`)
- `satisfies(node, completed)` — recursive boolean check
- `nodeProgress(node, completed)` — returns `{ done, total }`
- `courseCodes(node)` — flattens all course codes from a ReqNode tree

---

## API Routes

### `/api/courses`
- Fetches from UW Open API across 6 recent terms
- Deduplicates by course code; aggregates offered seasons
- In-memory cache: 1 hour; `revalidate: 86400`
- Timeout: 15 seconds (AbortController)
- Returns `CourseInfo[]` sorted by code

### `/api/parse-transcript`
- Accepts PDF via `multipart/form-data`
- Extracts course codes with regex: `/\b([A-Z]{2,8})\s{1,8}(\d{1,3}(?:[A-Z](?![a-z]))?)/g`
- Groups into terms by semester headers; falls back to flat list
- Returns `{ termCourses: Record<string, string[]> }`

---

## Data Files

### `requirements-filtered.json`
Programs keyed by opaque ID (e.g. `"HkeH1JRCjh"`). Each entry:
```json
{
  "id": "...",
  "name": "...",
  "faculty": "...",
  "code": "...",
  "isMinor": false,
  "isSpecialization": false,
  "isMathFaculty": true,
  "requirements": [/* ReqNode[] */]
}
```

### `antireqs.json`
Course code → array of conflicting codes: `{ "ACTSC445": ["ACTSC845"] }`.

### `invalid-combinations.json`
Used in `Onboarding.tsx` to block illegal program combos (e.g. Data Science cannot double-major).

---

## Program Selection Rules
- `MATH_MAJOR_IDS`: ~22 core Mathematics program IDs tracked as a `Set`
- `MATH_FACULTY_SUBJECTS`: `ACTSC, AMATH, CO, CS, MATBUS, MATH, PMATH, STAT`
- Joint Honours programs have bidirectional pairs in `JOINT_PAIRS`
- `getBlockedIds()` in Onboarding computes what programs can't be combined with the current selection

---

## Search Pattern
Use `fuzzysort` for any typeahead or program/course search:
```typescript
import fuzzysort from 'fuzzysort';
const results = fuzzysort.go(query, items, { key: 'name', limit: 5 });
```
Filter by subject prefix when the query contains digits (e.g. `CS 1` → only show CS courses).

---

## Code Style

- No comments unless the reason is non-obvious (a hidden constraint, a workaround, a subtle invariant)
- No docstrings or multi-line comment blocks
- No unused variables or imports
- Prefer `Set` and `Map` for membership checks and lookups over `.includes()` / `.find()` on large arrays
- Regex patterns for course codes: `/^([A-Z]+)(\d+)([A-Z]?)$/`
- Regex for term codes: `/^([WFS])(\d{2})$/`
- No `any`; use `unknown` + type narrowing when needed
- Async API route handlers should handle errors with try/catch and return appropriate HTTP status codes

---

## What Not To Do

- Do not use Tailwind classes for layout or component styling — use inline styles
- Do not introduce new state management libraries
- Do not mock the UW API in client code — go through `/api/courses`
- Do not add `console.log` debugging statements
- Do not create new data fetching patterns outside of the existing API route + context pattern
- Do not assume Next.js APIs match older versions — always verify against `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`
